ishmentReporter — committed - [39m                  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255minternal/engine/diag.go: dialResult enriched to use EstablishError.Reason — committed (working) - [39m                    [1B  [38;2;255;255;255minternal/engine/diag_establish_test.go — committed (compiles, passes) ## What needs doing ### 1. Implement [39m           [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mestablish_phase emission in conn.Dial In internal/conn/dial.go, after m.rt.Open returns successfully (line ~35, after[39m [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mroute is acquired), type-assert the transport as EstablishmentReporter. If it implements the interface, call [39m         [1B  [38;2;255;255;255m.Report(route.ID) to get the EstablishReport, then emit two diag.EstablishPhase events: - [39m                            [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mestablish_phase{tcp_connect, success/fail} — using report.TCPConnect for phase_ms - establish_phase{tls_handshake, [39m   [1B  [38;2;255;255;255msuccess/fail} — using report.TLSHandshake for phase_ms On Open failure (before Conn exists), emit the failed [39m         [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mestablish_phase from the same ids the engine holds. Key points from spec §4.2: - Emit OUTSIDE any transport/conn lock[39m [1B  [38;2;255;255;255m(report is read after Open returns; Emit is lock-free) - Use diag.EstablishPhase() constructor (see [39m                  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255minternal/diag/event.go:251) - Stamp with spec.AttemptID, spec.LocalAttemptID (already on the Conn literal at [39m         [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mdial.go:77) - transport field = diag.TransportTLS, direction = diag.DirOut - remote_endpoint from the dial address - [39m [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mThe Switch (m.rt) already proxies Report by global RouteID — check how conn.buildTelemetry type-asserts [39m              [1B  [38;2;255;255;255m(internal/conn/telemetry.go:76) for the pattern ### 2. Fix internal/conn/establish_emit_test.go This test file does [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mNOT compile. It uses APIs that don't exist. Fix it to use the real APIs: - conn.NewStubResponder() → does NOT exist. [39m [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mUse noiseik.NewResponder(identity, credential) like manager_integration_test.go:112 does. Import [39m                     [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mmeshynet/internal/handshake/noiseik. - conn.NewStubInitiator(b.X25519Pub()) → does NOT exist. Use [39m                    [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mnoiseik.NewInitiator(identity, credential, peerX25519Pub) like manager_integration_test.go:124. - b.X25519Pub() → [39m    [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mdoes NOT exist. Use b.X25519Static() which returns (priv, pub [32]byte) — you need only the pub. - c.Close() → Conn [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mhas NO Close method. Use c.Retire(nil) + <-c.Done() or just rely on mgrA.Close() cleanup. - admitAll2 → remove, [39m      [1B  [38;2;255;255;255madmitAll already exists in manager_integration_test.go (same package conn_test). - Unused variables a (line 38) and [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mrtB (line 160) — remove or use them. - mkIdentity2 → redundant, mkIdentity already exists in [39m                         [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mmanager_integration_test.go (same package). Use that. - The test is in package conn_test (NOT package conn), so it [39m   [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mcannot use unexported stubResponderHS/stubInitiatorHS. Must use noiseik real handshakes. Look at [39m                     [1B  [38;2;255;255;255minternal/conn/manager_integration_test.go for the CORRECT pattern of setting up a TLS dial test with real noiseik [39m    [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mhandshakes, identity, credential, and RouteTLS. The test TestInitiatorEstablishPhase_TLS_DialSuccess should follow [39m   [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mthat pattern but use RouteTLS (not RouteMem) and attach a diagtest.Collector via WithEmitter. ### 3. The third test [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255m(TestEngineEstablishPhase_RefusedDial) is currently t.Skip — leave it skipped for now, that's fine. ## Verification [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mRun these and make sure they all pass: go test ./internal/conn/... -run TestInitiatorEstablishPhase -v go test [39m       [1B  [38;2;255;255;255m./internal/conn/... go test ./internal/engine/... go test ./internal/transport/... go build ./... All must pass. Do [39m  [1B  [38;2;255;255;255mNOT run git commit — just make the code work and report what you changed.[39m                                             [2B[49m[38;2;215;119;87m✶[3G[38;2;235;159;127mM[38;2;215;119;87marinating… [3B[38;2;153;153;153m❯ [39m[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l]777;notify;warp://cli-agent;{"v":1,"agent":"claude","event":"prompt_submit","session_id":"48f0ca16-130d-4ca8-817c-856c36e01bb8","cwd":"/Users/shady/Documents/repos/meshynet","project":"meshynet","query":"Implement T3 (no1.3): initiator establishment-phase emission in conn.Manager.Dial, and fix the test file that verifies it. ## Context This is the meshynet project (Go). We're on branch phase-no1.3 ..."}]0;⠐ Claude Code]0;⠂ Claude Code]0;⠐ Claude Code]0;⠂ Claude Code]0;⠐ Claude Code]0;⠂ Claude Code[?2026h[?25l[H[102C[35B[K[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l]0;⠐ Claude Code]0;⠂ Claude Code[?2026h[?25l[H[2C[39B[38;2;255;193;7m⏵⏵ auto mode on[38;2;153;153;153m (shift+tab to cycle) · esc to interrupt · ← for agents[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l]0;⠐ Claude Code[?2026h[?25l[H[2C[34B[38;2;215;119;87mR[5Gzzm[10Gazzin[38;2;235;159;127mg…[38;2;215;119;87m [39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l]0;⠂ Claude Code]0;⠂ Implement T3 establish-phase emission and fix test file[?2026h[?25l[H[34B[38;2;215;119;87m✽[15Gg…[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l[?2026h[?25l[H[34B[38;2;210;110;84m✻[3GRazzmatazzing… [39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l]0;⠐ Implement T3 establish-phase emission and fix test file[?2026h[?25l[H[34B[38;2;210;110;84m✶[39m[40;1H[38;3H[?25h[?2026l[?2026